:::: {.columns}

::: {.column width="50%"}
![](minefield.jpg)
:::
::: {.column width="50%"}
- Antiquated attitudes

- Non-representative sampling

- Exclusionary methodologies

- Uninterpretable AI models
:::
::::


## {.winter}

"Even if AI systems are designed by unbiased coders striving for neutrality,
those systems derive data from and exist within a medical system that has its
own antiminority culture; those views are embedded in the patters that AI
learns."

![](Bracic.png)

::: {.footer}
[Bracic et al](https://www.science.org/doi/10.1126/science.abo2788)
:::

## Race is more than a data column {.winter}

![](azimi1.png)

::: {.footer}
[Azimi et al](https://academic.oup.com/jalm/article-abstract/8/1/113/6845827)
:::



## Race is more than a data column {.winter}

- Even when race is removed from a dataset, statistical models can reliably predict a patient's race from the way the physician wrote about them. ([Keeling et al](https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.04008))

- If bias is already creeping through, a statistical model will only exacerbate it.



